eyersipping
It was only five years ago that we introduced Cybersipping to the aviation world. It
was so exciting to find web sites that could teach wine. I thought those sites were
unbelievable, and now at a frightening speed five years later web sites on wine
number are in the ten thousands. Our goal was to bring you the best to make
your wine education more fun, especially if you travel a lot and sometimes find
yourself stuck in a hotel with time on your hands. You could go on line and study
wine all day long! There are now so many incredible sites for you to choose from;
a new one appears every day. As an educator this is music to my ears!
Here are two great sites that you should bookmark.
www.wineeducation.org
I like this site because it caters to both beginners and advanced students of the
grape. The site has been around for about eight years and takes a nice and easy
approach to the joy of learning about wine. You get the sense that there is some
passion behind this site.
www.drinkwine.com
This professionally done site has it all, from winery directories to travel in wine
country. It is well laid out and easy to follow and read. Gives you wine clubs to
join and the latest news in the business. You can ask questions on wine and get
answers. Very practical.
